text.text: We stopped by this hotel on our way back to Pune. They mainly serve thalis, so we ordered the mutton thali and the Maharashtrian Vej thali. The mutton thali was delicious, as recommended by my friends, but the Vej thali was just okay. It had akhha masoor, paneer sabji with roti, and dal rice. The paneer wasn't soft and seemed stale. The ambience was nice, and the place wasn't too crowded. The service was good too. Overall, I didn't enjoy the Vej thali much, but I would recommend trying their non-veg thali. You can give this place a visit.
